com.opengamma.strata.basics.index

Class ImmutableFloatingRateName

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.basics.index.ImmutableFloatingRateName
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FloatingRateName, Named, Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class ImmutableFloatingRateName
extends Object
implements FloatingRateName, ImmutableBean, Serializable
    An immutable floating rate index name, such as Libor, Euribor or US Fed Fund.

    This is the standard immutable implementation of FloatingRateName.

    See Also:

      • getName

        public String getName()
        Description copied from interface: FloatingRateName
        Gets the name that uniquely identifies this index.

        This name is used in serialization and can be parsed using FloatingRateName.of(String). It will be the external name, typically from FpML, such as 'GBP-LIBOR-BBA'.

        public String getIndexName()
